===Etymology===
Hindi '''[[चीता]]''' (''cītā'') "leopard, panther", ultimately from Sanskrit '''[[चित्र]]''' (''citra'') "multicolored, speckled" + '''[[काय]]''' (''kāya'') "body", thus "having a spotted body".

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /ˈtʃiːtə/
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːtə|-iːtə]]

====Homophones====
*[[cheater]] (''in [[non-rhotic]] accents'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#A large [[cat]] (''[[Acinonyx jubatus]]''), native to Africa, credited with being the fastest terrestrial animal.

